 private diary, an introduction and notes by his daughter, and a selection of personal family photographs complete this compelling volume.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAtomic bombzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aScience and statezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Letters.2bisacsh1 aHeisenberg, Elisabeth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHeisenberg, Irene1 aHirsch-Heisenberg, Anna Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300225013423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300225013.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles